summary: This document appears to be a text message exchange between an FBI agent and a witness or associate. The witness states they have already told everything they know and were not present during certain events except when a housekeeper was there. The agent presses for a follow-up meeting to put pieces together.

persons.name: NIA
persons.context: The agent is attempting to schedule a follow-up meeting with a witness, stating they are putting pieces together and have flexible timing.

events.title: Text message exchange regarding investigation
events.description: An FBI agent and a witness exchange text messages about scheduling a follow-up meeting for the investigation. The witness claims to have already disclosed all information.

keyFacts: A witness claims to have already told investigators everything they know about the events in question.
The witness states that during the relevant time, only a housekeeper was present, and no one else was there.
FBI agents are attempting to schedule a follow-up meeting to ask additional questions and 'put all the pieces together'.
The document is subject to a protective order restricting certain paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
